      "text": "The hawala system has existed since the 8th century between Arabic and Muslim traders alongside the [[Silk Road]] and beyond as a protection against theft. It is believed to have arisen in the financing of long-distance trade around the emerging capital trade centers in the early medieval period. In [[South Asia]], it appears to have developed into a fully-fledged money market instrument, which was only gradually replaced by the instruments of the formal banking system ([[bank]]) in the first half of the 20th century."
